-- Chelsea to Bid for Roma’s De Rossi, Mirror Says: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-07-04T09:00:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-04/chelsea-to-bid-for-roma-s-de-rossi-mirror-says-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers with clickable Internet links.  De Rossi Bid  Chelsea plans to bid 10 million pounds ($15.3 million) to
sign AS Roma midfielder Daniele de Rossi, the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  De Rossi is “increasingly disaffected” at Roma after
falling out with supporters, the Mirror said.  Ronaldo Stays  Cristiano Ronaldo has ruled out returning to Manchester
United for now,  the Guardian  reported.  The Real Madrid forward, who moved to Spain for a record 80
million pounds in 2009, said he is “really, really happy”
playing in La Liga, according to the newspaper.  City Striker  Manchester City may pay as much as 28 million pounds to
sign Sevilla striker Alvaro Negredo, the  Daily Express  reported.  City spent 15 million pounds to acquire his former Sevilla
teammate Jesus Navas earlier in the offseason, the Express said.  QPR Move  Queens Park Rangers wants to sign Tottenham’s Scott Parker,
the  London Evening Standard  reported.  Tottenham is asking for about 2 million pounds to trade the
32-year-old, who is also attracting interest from Sunderland and
Fulham, the Standard said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Alex Duff in  Madrid   at
